Introduction

Han Jisung is a South Korean rapper, dancer, singer-songwriter, and composer under JYP Entertainment. He is best known as one of the main rappers and music producers of the group Stray Kids. He is also part of the hip-hop rap unit 3RACHA.

In late 2016, HAN, under the stage name "J.One," formed the hip-hop group 3RACHA with fellow trainees Bang Chan and Changbin. They released self-produced music on SoundCloud throughout 2017. On October 13, 2017, JYP Entertainment officially introduced HAN by revealing his picture and name, announcing his participation in the survival show Stray Kids, where he took on roles as a rapper, vocalist, and producer. By the final episode on December 19, 2017, it was confirmed that HAN would debut as a member of the boy group Stray Kids.

Han debuted as a member of Stray Kids on March 25, 2018, with I Am Not and its title track "District 9".
